{"lemma":"نَفَرَ","slug":"نَفَرَ","root":"ن.ف.ر","root_slug":"ن-ف-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ف-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"نَفَرَ","root":"نفر","pos":"V","occurrence_count":8},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":8,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":19},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40221"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shy, to bolt, to stampede"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to flee, to run away, to turn tail, to scamper, to abscond, to get away, to escape"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to break loose, to recoil, to slip away, to free oneself, to get free, to break away, to free"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have an aversion, to have a distaste"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hate intensely, to dislike, to be disinclined to, to feel disgust for, to have an aversion to, to detest, to abhor, to loathe"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to avoid, to shun, to eschew"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hurry, to rush, to hasten"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bulge, to swell, to jut out, to protrude, to stand out, to stick out"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to startle, to frighten, to scare away, to frighten away, to drive away, to chase away"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shy, to bolt, to stampede"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to alienate, to estrange, to deter, to make dissatisfied"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make averse to, to make disinclined to, to make hateful to, to alienate from, to make someone hate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَفَرَ (nafara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"band, party, group, troop, herd, coterie, collective, cohort, clique, company, association, society, gang, flock, circle, cabal, squad, community, crowd"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"unit, troop"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"soldier, private, man"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"guy, individual, person, gent, persona"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a dry measure, ¹⁄₈ of a ثُمْنَة (ṯumna), ¹⁄₆₄ of a قَدَح (qadaḥ)","tags":["Yemen"],"examples":[{"text":"صاح: «نفر بيض… يأكل». جلب له النادل الثاني شاياً أحمر.","english":"He yelled: “A nafar of eggs … he eats.” The second waiter brought red tea to him."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"plural of نَافِر (nāfir, “shy, fearful, timid”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40221","headword_ar":"نَفَرَ","root":"nfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, L, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, K,) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naforN","text_ar":"نَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafaraAnN","text_ar":"نَفَرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nufuwrN","text_ar":"نُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) said of a wild animal, (T, Msb,) a gazelle, (M, K,) or other beast, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took fright, and fled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ran away at random;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became refractory, and went away at random;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ran away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broke loose, and went hither and thither by reason of his sprightliness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arada","text_ar":"شَرَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astnfr","text_ar":"استنفر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, Msb, K;) and so the former verb"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in"},{"kind":"text","text":"speaking of a camel, or a beast: (L, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$rd","text_ar":"شرد"},{"kind":"text","text":":) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafarati Ald~aAb~apu","text_ar":"نَفَرَتِ الدَّابَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, A, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nufuwrN","text_ar":"نُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nifaArN","text_ar":"نِفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, A, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naforN","text_ar":"نَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) or this signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the beast was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, impatient"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shied at it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and retired to a distance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isotinofaArN","text_ar":"اـِسْتِنْفَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nufuwrN","text_ar":"نُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafara","text_ar":"نَفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"page_break","n":2824},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nifaArN","text_ar":"نِفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nufuwrN","text_ar":"نُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he fled, and went away"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aside"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apart"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a distance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafara","text_ar":"نَفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nufuwrN","text_ar":"نُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nifaArN","text_ar":"نِفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naforN","text_ar":"نَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafiyrN","text_ar":"نَفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as used in the following phrases.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafarotu mino h`*aA AlA^amori","text_ar":"نَفَرْتُ مِنْ هٰذَا الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I shrank from this thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair; was averse from it; did not like"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approve it."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafara fulaAnN mino SuHobapi","text_ar":"نَفَرَ فُلَانٌ مِنْ صُحْبَةِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one shrank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was averse, from the companionship of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the associating with, such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafarati AlmaroA^apu mino zawojihaA","text_ar":"نَفَرَتِ المَرْاَةُ مِنْ زَوْجِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The woman was averse from her husband;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shunned"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avoided him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (All from the A.) And you say of a man's disposition,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eani AlHaq~i","text_ar":"عَنِ الحَقِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanaf~ara","text_ar":"تَنَفَّرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It shunned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was averse from, the truth"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Bd, lxvii. 21.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_il~aA nufuwrFA","text_ar":"اـِلَّا نُفُورًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur, [xvii. 43, and xxxv. 40,] means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Save in aversion"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafiyrN","text_ar":"نَفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nufuwrN","text_ar":"نُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the subst. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafarN","text_ar":"نَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with two fet-hahs. (Msb) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafara Al$~aYo'u mina Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"نَفَرَ الشَّىْءُ مِنَ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nifaArN","text_ar":"نِفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nufuwrN","text_ar":"نُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thing receded, withdrew, removed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became remote"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aloof, from the thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, T, S.) [See also 3.] ―         -b5-  Hence it is, I think, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafara","text_ar":"نَفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as signifying (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It became swollen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the following words of a trad. of 'Omar:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taxal~ala rajulN fiY zamaAnihi","text_ar":"تَخَلَّلَ رَجُلٌ فِى زَمَانِهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlqaSabi fanafara fuwhu","text_ar":"بِالقَصَبِ فَنَفَرَ فُوهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man, in his time, picked his teeth with reeds, and in consequence his mouth became swollen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though the flesh, disliking the disease, receded from it, and so became swollen. (A'Obeyd, T, S. *) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafarati AlEayonu","text_ar":"نَفَرَتِ العَيْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nufuwrN","text_ar":"نُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His eye became inflamed and swollen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so you say of other parts of the person. (M, K. *) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafara AljuroHu","text_ar":"نَفَرَ الجُرْحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wound became swollen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became so after healing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(W, i. 42.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafara Aljilodu","text_ar":"نَفَرَ الجِلْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The skin became swollen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the flesh receded from it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) [All these significations seem to be derived from the first in this art.: and so several others which follow.] ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafarotu A_ilaY A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"نَفَرْتُ اـِلَى ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nifaArN","text_ar":"نِفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I betook myself to God by reason of fear, seeking protection."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafaruwA","text_ar":"نَفَرُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naforN","text_ar":"نَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They became separated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, * Msb, K: *) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafarto","text_ar":"نَفَرتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of camels. (TA.) Hence, (M,) the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytuhu qabola kul~i SayoHK wanaforK","text_ar":"لَقِيتُهُ قَبْلَ كُلِّ صَيْحٍ وَنَفْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A.) a proverb, in which the last word is used tropically; (A;) explained in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SyH","text_ar":"صيح"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (S.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDiba mino gayori SayoHK walaA nafKro","text_ar":"غَضِبَ مِنْ غَيْرِ صَيْحٍ وَلَا نَفٍرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; explained in the same art.] ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafara AlHaAj~u mino minFY","text_ar":"نَفَرَ الحَاجُّ مِنْ مِنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naforN","text_ar":"نَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafarN","text_ar":"نَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nufuwrN","text_ar":"نُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafiyrN","text_ar":"نَفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pilgrims removed from Minè."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu Aln~afori","text_ar":"يَوْمُ النَّفْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~afari","text_ar":"النَّفَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~afuwri","text_ar":"النَّفُورِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~afiyri","text_ar":"النَّفِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapu Aln~afori","text_ar":"لَيْلَةُ النَّفْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~afari","text_ar":"النَّفَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The day of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the night immediately preceding, the removing from Minè"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after the day called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu Alqar~i","text_ar":"يَوْمُ القَرِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S;) [therefore."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the twelfth of Dhu-l-Hijjeh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or there are two days thus called: (Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu Aln~afori AlA^aw~alu","text_ar":"يَوْمُ النَّفْرِ الاَوَّلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [the day above mentioned,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the second of the days called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ay~aAmu","text_ar":"اَيَّامُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~a$oriyqi","text_ar":"التَّشْرِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAth, Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu Aln~afor AlA~xiru","text_ar":"يَوْمُ النَّفْر الاّخِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAth,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~aAniY","text_ar":"الثَّانِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the third thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, Msb:) the order is this;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu Aln~aHori","text_ar":"يَوْمُ النَّحْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", then"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu Alqar~i","text_ar":"يَوْمُ القَرِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", then"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu Aln~afor AlA^aw~alu","text_ar":"يَوْمُ النَّفْر الاَوَّلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"then"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu","text_ar":"يَوْمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~afori AlA=xiru","text_ar":"النَّفْرِ الا=خِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, L) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafaruwA fiY AlA^amori","text_ar":"نَفَرُوا فِى الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M.) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liloA^amori","text_ar":"لِلْاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K.) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nufuwrN","text_ar":"نُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nifArN","text_ar":"نِفارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafiyrN","text_ar":"نَفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Zj, M, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tnAfrwA","text_ar":"تنافروا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away, to execute the affair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlqitaAli","text_ar":"فِى القِتَالِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to fight."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqaruwA","text_ar":"نَقَرُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":", alone,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They went forth to war against unbelievers"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"So in the Kur, is 82."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaAlwA laA tanofiruwA","text_ar":"وَقَالوا لَا تَنْفِرُوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY AlHr~i qulo naArN jahan~ama A^a$adN Har~aA","text_ar":"فى الحرِّ قُلْ نَارٌ جَهَنَّمَ اَشَدٌ حَرَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they said, Go not ye forth to war against the unbelievers in the heat: say, The fire of hell is hotter"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and so in the same chap. v. 39: (Jel:) and in the same book, iv. 73. (Bd.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafaruwA lahumo","text_ar":"نَفَرُوا لَهُمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They went forth to fight them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, from a trad.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tafaruwA A_ilY AlHarob","text_ar":"تَفَرُوا اـِلى الحَرْب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They hastened to the war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to war."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b10-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafawuA maEahu","text_ar":"نَفَوُا مَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anofaruwhu","text_ar":"اَنْفَرُوهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inofaArN","text_ar":"اـِنْفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They aided and succoured them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or the former verb, alone,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they,"},{"kind":"text","text":"being asked to do so,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complied, and went forth to aid."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafrabinaA","text_ar":"نَفرَبِنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2."}],"source_refs":["T","M","L","Msb","K","S","A","TA","IKtt","IAth","Jel"]}]}}